FAILURE FIX #3 – React UI Race Conditions
Problem
Frontend (React) components—like Terminal.jsx or StatusOverlay.jsx—might attempt to fetch memory or status data before the backend is fully ready, causing null states, blank screens, or runtime warnings. Fix Overview
Create a /status API endpoint in FastAPI that reports system readiness
Use useEffect() in React to poll until backend is marked “ready”
Delay rendering core components until that flag is confirmed
Backend File: main.py (or routes/system.py)
